*User Story / Description:*

When a user with a *cancelled Factor subscription* navigates to the Supplements/FactorForm products page, the application enters a perpetual loop. The {{discount_comm_id}} parameter is repeatedly added and removed from the URL, causing the UI to glitch (banners flashing) and preventing product prices from loading.

This issue appears to be specific to the *cancelled state*; reactivating the subscription resolves the behavior.

For further details:

[https://hellofresh.slack.com/archives/C06AW0AA9NE/p1768389111873749|https://hellofresh.slack.com/archives/C06AW0AA9NE/p1768389111873749|smart-link] 

*Steps:*

* Log in to a Factor account with an active subscription.
* *Deactivate/Cancel* the main Factor subscription.
* Navigate to the *Supplements* tab or use a URL containing the {{discount_comm_id}} parameter.
* Observe the URL cycling and the UI flickering/missing price data.
{panel}

{panel:bgColor=#e3fcef}
*Acceptance Criteria:*

* The Supplements page should load normally for cancelled users, displaying accurate product information and stable UI components.

